<h3>Pattern Parameters</h3>
<p>Pattern parameters are a means to hydrate data in an included pattern, but <strong>not further downstream</strong>. They are yet another option for hydrating patterns with varying degrees of granularity.</p>
<p>Parameters are a <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/feplet" target="_blank">Feplet</a> feature. Parameters are an <em>add-on</em> to a mostly standards-adherent implementation of Mustache. The only <em>divergence</em> from the Mustache standard is Feplet's forbidding of spaces between opening braces <code>&lcub;&lcub;</code> and any control character, e.g. <code>#</code>, <code>/</code>, <code>&gt;</code>, etc.</p>
<h4>Pattern Parameter Syntax</h4>
<p>The keys listed in the pattern parameters need to match variable names in the included pattern. The values listed for each key will replace the variables. For example:</p>
<h6>components-top-level:</h6>
<pre><code>&lcub;&lcub;> compounds-mid-level(content: 'Mid-level only') }}</code></pre>
<h6>compounds-mid-level:</h6>
<pre><code>&lt;p>&lcub;&lcub; content }}&lt;/p>
&lcub;&lcub;> elements-bottom-level }}</code></pre>
<h6>elements-bottom-level:</h6>
<pre><code>&lt;p>&lcub;&lcub; content }}&lt;/p></code></pre>
<h6>Rendered as:</h6>
<pre><code>&lt;p>Mid-level only&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;/p></code></pre>
<h4>Advanced Syntax</h4>
<p>Parameters can be any valid <a href="http://json5.org" target="_blank">JSON5</a>, minus the exterior curly braces:</p>
<pre><code>&lcub;&lcub;> patternType-patternName(
  bool: false,
  num: 0,
  str: 'string',
  'str w spaces': "string with 'single quotes'",
  "str-w_special~char?": true
) }}</code></pre>
<p>You can even submit objects as values, but be sure to space curly braces so they are not mistaken for closing tags <code>}}</code></p>
<pre><code>&lcub;&lcub;> patternType-patternName(
  obj: { deeperObj: { "valid?": true } }
) }}</code></pre>
